		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The important difference is that Moore's Law used to mean that &quot;Uses all the resources of 3-year-old hardware&quot; would imply &quot;Works fantastically on current hardware&quot;. Not true anymore.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
